<li id="cite_note-59"><b><a href="#cite_ref-59" title="">^</a></b> V.A. Gunasekara, <a href="http://www.buddhistinformation.com/buddhist_attitude_to_god.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.buddhistinformation.com/buddhist_attitude_to_god.htm" rel="nofollow">The Buddhist Attitude to God.</a> In the Bhuridatta Jataka, "The Buddha argues that the three most commonly given attributes of God, viz. omnipotence, omniscience and benevolence towards humanity cannot all be mutually compatible with the existential fact of dukkha."</li>
